=== Tokorozawa City–designated cultural properties ===
* Tangible cultural properties
** Monument inscribed with a poem on the Mikoto-zakura<ref>{{Cite web|Japanese|url=http://www.city.tokorozawa.saitama.jp/iitokoro/enjoy/bunkakyoyo/bunkazai/shishiteibunkazai/meisyo/bunzai_20100601150043467.html |title=Poem Monument of the Mikoto-zakura |publisher=Tokorozawa City Board of Education, Cultural Properties Protection Division |accessdate=2015-06}}</ref> (Place of scenic beauty) – Erected in {{jalink|Kyōwa|Q960763}} 2 ({{jalink|1802|Q6883}}); the oldest poem monument in the city.
** Medieval documents of Kitano Tenjinsha<ref>{{Cite web|Japanese|url=https://www.city.tokorozawa.saitama.jp/iitokoro/enjoy/bunkakyoyo/bunkazai/shishiteibunkazai/komonjo/bunzai_20100810104554996.html |title=Medieval Documents of Kitano Tenjinsha |publisher=Tokorozawa City Board of Education, Cultural Properties Protection Division |accessdate=2015-06}}</ref> (Ancient documents) – Eleven documents including a land donation charter by {{jalink|Ashikaga Ujimitsu|Q4306934}}.

