=== Annual festivals ===
* New Year’s Day Festival ({{jalink|January 1|Q2150}}) – Prayer amulets are distributed.
* {{jalink|Hatsumōde|Q1032381}} ({{jalink|January 1|Q2150}})
* {{jalink|Setsubun Festival}} ({{jalink|February 3|Q2315}}) – Corresponds to the shrine’s Great Purification; “Shikinaisha Kitano Shrine Great Purification Amulets” are distributed.
* {{jalink|Hatsuuma|Q510847}} Festival ({{jalink|February 11|Q2335}}) – Held at the Inari Shrine; “Inari Shrine Amulets” are distributed.
* Prayer for Harvest Festival ({{jalink|February 27|Q2361}}) – Also called Toshigoi-no-matsuri; “Prayer for Harvest Amulets” are distributed.
* Spring Grand Festival ({{jalink|March 21|Q2433}}) – Paired with the Autumn Grand Festival and regarded as the most important festival of the shrine; “Kuniichi Chigi Shrine Good Fortune and Protection Amulets” are distributed.
* Spring Festival ({{jalink|March 25|Q2454}}) – Also called Niban-machi; “Mononobe Tenjinsha Amulets” are distributed.
* {{jalink|Sericulture|Q11236}} Festival ({{jalink|April 3|Q2509}}) – Held at the Ayako Tenjinsha; “Ayako Tenjinsha Amulets” are distributed.
* Memorial Service ({{jalink|April 15|Q2497}}) – Held at the Kotesashi Shrine to console the spirits of local war dead since the Sino-Japanese and Russo-Japanese wars.
* Yakumo Festival – Eve festival on {{jalink|July 14|Q2691}}, main festival on {{jalink|July 15|Q2686}}; “Yakumo Shrine Disaster-Prevention Amulets” are distributed.
* Autumn Grand Festival (late September) – Hayashi music is offered every year, and Satokagura is offered every two years.
* {{jalink|Niiname Festival|Q11501518}} ({{jalink|November 23|Q3021}}) – “Niiname Festival Amulets” are distributed.<ref>{{Cite web|Japanese|url=https://kitanotenjin.com/nenkangyouji.html |title=Festivals of Kitano Tenjinsha |publisher=Kitano Tenjinsha |accessdate=2022-01-15}}</ref>

